      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# **Fancy indexing: Coordinates**\n",
        "\n",
        "Example: `x` has dimension 4. We choose the following coordinates `x[i,j,k,l]`:\n",
        "\n",
        "* Indexing on `(i,k) = (0,3), (1,3), (0,1), (0,1), (1,2), (0,2)`\n",
        "\n",
        "* Slicing on `j: [:]`\n",
        "\n",
        "* Slicing on `l: [1:-1:2]`"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "GfzBe1Epctnu"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "x = torch.arange(64).reshape(4,4,4)\n",
        "print(x)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Coordinates fancy indexing\n",
        "y = x[1, [3,3,1], [0,2,1]]\n",
        "print(y)\n",
        "print(y.shape)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
